      </figure>
    </div>

    <section class="blog-section u-spaceChildren u-paddingMd u-paddingTopNone">
      <p>It’s not about being an expert at both design and development. You will always have a strong leaning towards one or the other. I will always be a designer first. I will never look at something and not want to make it beautiful. Also, there are developers out there that not only can see and appreciate design, but can put together <a href="#">typographic systems</a> and pick amazing color palettes, however, at their core they are developers. People have their natural strengths, but that doesn't preclude them from having other talents and appreciations.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="hang">
      <figure class="hang-right">
        <img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/q9IXJJklK7lpm/giphy.gif" alt="sexy unicorn" />
